<TITLE> Bush welcomes Bangladesh election roadmap </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, July 26 (bdnews24.com)US President George W Bush has welcomed the election roadmap and expressed his appreciation for the caretaker government's efforts in "sticking to its promise to hold elections in 2008". Bush also assured Bangladesh of US assistance "in any way" for the upcoming elections, the foreign ministry said in a statement Thursday. The US president made these remarks on receiving credentials from the newly appointed Bangladeshi ambassador to the USA, M Humayan Kabir, at the White House on July 25. Citing Bangladesh as "an example of a moderate and tolerant Muslim nation", Bush stated that the country had affirmed and reaffirmed its dedication to democratic principles in numerous elections. He acknowledged the reform efforts of the current caretaker government, stating: "We support your efforts to fight corruption and collect taxes." The US president also expressed his support for granting duty and quota free access to Bangladeshi garments products in the USA, to promote the continued economic development of Bangladesh. bdn
